Description: Hail to the mighty iron label - Replay Guitar Exchange presents this Ibanez Iron Label RGAIX6FM in a chilling White Frost Flat color. This compact yet beastly model is built with a flamed maple top, with a mahogany body and a smooth Nitro Wizard three-piece maple/bubinga neck that hosts a bound ebony fingerboard. A set of Dimarzio Fusion Edge humbuckers produce a killer heavy tone, controlled by a three-way switch blade - all topped off with a set of locking Gotoh MG-T tuners. This model is in Very Good condition, hosting a small ding on the back horn, and an estimated 95% of fret life remaining. The Iron Label is ready to donate itself to the church of metal, available now at Replay Guitar Exchange! As always, feel free to contact our store for more details, or with any questions.
